HEADWORD: Myriare
<hw>Myr"i*are</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Myria-</er>, and 2d <er>Are</er>.]</ety> <def>A measure of surface
in the metric system containing ten thousand ares, or one million square
meters. It is equal to about 247.1 acres.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

